      {
        "id": "30322a8b-3ad6-4af3-badf-5d71d2b31d93",
        "score": 0.6381501,
        "text": "The document is a page from the CAISO Business Practice Manual for Scheduling Coordinator Certification and Termination. It includes a \"Scheduling Coordinator Application Form\" for certification by the California Independent System Operator Corporation (CAISO) under the CAISO Tariff. The application is confidential and consists of two main sections:\n\n1. **Section I: Administrative Requirements**\n   - **Applicant's Legal Name**: Must be consistent across all documentation to avoid delays.\n   - **Scheduling Coordinator ID (SCID)**: Applicants must provide three options for their SCID, which is a unique identifier in CAISO Market systems.\n   - **Address Details**: Includes street address, city, state, and zip code.\n   - **State of Incorporation or Partnership**: If applicable.\n   - **Proposed Commencement Date for Service**: When the service is expected to start.\n   - **Entity Type**: Options include municipal utility, power marketer, investor-owned utility, etc.\n   - **Use of Scheduling Agent Services**: Applicants must indicate if they plan to use these services.\n\n2. **Section II: Scheduling Coordinator Customer Information**\n   - Applicants must certify their authorization to represent Generators and Loads as Scheduling Coordinator Customers.\n   - They must confirm that:\n     - Generators have entered into necessary agreements with CAISO.\n     - UDCs have entered into UDC Operating Agreements with CAISO.\n     - CAISO Metered Entities have entered into Meter Service Agreements.\n     - Wholesale Customers are eligible for service.\n     - Each End-Use Customer is eligible for service as a Direct Access End User.\n   - Applicants seeking to serve as Scheduling Coordinators for Convergence Bidding Entities must certify their authorization to represent these entities.\n\nThe document is effective from March 1, 2025, and is version 16.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Business_Practice_Manual_for_Scheduling_Coordinator_Certification_&_Termination_and_Convergence_Bidding_Entity_Registration_&_Termination/page_53.jpg",
