      {
        "id": "8b9accff-8d26-4057-9e47-4b7ffeef01f8",
        "score": 0.6190506,
        "text": "The document is from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff, specifically Section 8, dated August 3, 2024. It outlines performance and operational standards for electricity resources.\n\n1. **Regulation Up and Down**: A minimum performance threshold of 25% is required for resources offering Regulation Up and Down capacity. If a resource's accuracy falls below this threshold, it must re-certify within 90 days. Data from intervals with lost accuracy will not be used for performance calculations.\n\n2. **Spinning and Non-Spinning Reserves**: The CAISO must maintain a minimum contingency Operating Reserve, adhering to NERC and WECC reliability standards. The CAISO may apply stricter criteria as needed.\n\n3. **Voltage Support**: The CAISO determines daily voltage support requirements to maintain voltage levels and reactive margins. Dispatch instructions are issued to ensure grid reliability. All generating units must comply with power factor requirements as per contractual arrangements or applicable tariffs.\n\nParticipating Generators must adhere to CAISO's specified voltage schedules and power factor ranges as per their interconnection agreements.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Fifth_Replacement_FERC_Electric_Tariff/page_152.jpg",
