        "text": "The document outlines the requirements for Local Capacity and Peak Demand validation for Load Serving Entities (LSEs) and Community Choice Aggregators (CPEs) as per the California Independent System Operator (CAISO) guidelines. \n\n1. **Tariff Section 40.7.a.i**: Each LSE or CPE must ensure they have procured sufficient megawatt (MW) capacity for each Transmission Access Charge (TAC) area where they have obligations. This involves meeting MW responsibilities by procuring the necessary capacity in any Local Capacity Area (LCA) within the TAC area.\n\n2. **Tariff Section 40.7.a.ii**: The Scheduling Coordinator (SC) for an LSE must identify all resources used to meet the forecasted peak monthly demand and reserve margin for the relevant reporting period.\n\nThe document is part of the CAISO Business Practice Manual for Reliability Requirements, last revised on March 12, 2025.",
