        "text": "The document outlines the requirements and examples for energy resources in relation to Regulation Energy Management. It specifies that resources must be able to generate or consume energy for 15 minutes after a Dispatch Instruction. If not, they must meet the same certification requirements as generators.\n\nTwo examples illustrate this:\n\n1. A fully charged resource with 5 MWh can discharge 20 MW for 15 minutes, equating to 20 MW of regulation up capacity.\n2. A completely discharged resource with 2.5 MWh can consume 10 MW for 15 minutes, equating to 10 MW of regulation down capacity.\n\nResources not using Regulation Energy Management are certified like generators.\n\nThe document also provides scenarios for performance evaluation:\n\n- Example A: A resource meets the performance threshold for two consecutive months.\n- Example B: A resource fails to meet the threshold in one of two consecutive months.\n- Examples C & D: A resource meets the threshold in one month, then provides fewer intervals in subsequent months before meeting the threshold again.\n\nA table is included to track the number of intervals provided, performance threshold compliance, and actions taken.",
